  "subject": "feat: physical iceberg maintenance via trino and data-layer freshness gate",
  "body": "pyiceberg 0.11.1 only expires snapshot metadata (no orphan-file API on this\npin, per maintenance.py's existing docstring); Trino OPTIMIZE/expire_\nsnapshots/remove_orphan_files is the load-bearing physical GC (final review\nelevated this to Plan 3). Verified live against the pinned Trino 476 (docs\npage + a real probe pod): exact procedure syntax, the 7d retention floor\n(matches our chosen threshold exactly, no config change needed), and --\npreviously unproven -- that Lakekeeper's vended S3 credentials permit LIST\n(remove_orphan_files needs it; proven both against a live alice.job_info\ntable and a dedicated scratch-table probe with independent before/after S3\nobject counts via s3fs).\n\ningest-maintenance CronWorkflow becomes a 2-step DAG (pyiceberg expiry then\nTrino physical maintenance); ingest-nightly gains a third step,\ncheck-freshness, completing design D11's data-layer staleness check (D11\nalerting only covered \"the CronWorkflow stopped firing\" until now -- a\nsuccessful-looking nightly run that never actually committed a fresh\nsnapshot was previously invisible). IcebergSnapshotStale documents the\nexit-code path, same honest no-new-components annotation style as\nRetentionUnverifiedRows (per Task 3 in\ndeliverables/plans/2026-07-12-datalake-v2-query-plan.md).\n\n(per Task 3 in deliverables/plans/2026-07-12-datalake-v2-query-plan.md)\n"
